  <name>Tins</name>
  <summary>Containers just like Virtual Machines</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
        Use all benefits of virtual machines - but in lightweight containers.
    </p>
    <blockquote>
        <strong>Tins:</strong> tinplate containers - often used to package breath mints.
        In some cultures, these boxes are referred to as "tins".
    </blockquote>
    <p>
        Features:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Create/destroy containers</li>
        <li>Start/stop containers</li>
        <li>Open container shell</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong> Until <a href="https://github.com/marbetschar/tins/issues/7">issue #7</a>
        is fixed, Tins expects LXD to be installed via apt and initialized on the host system.
        To do so, please execute the following commands in your terminal:
    </p>
    <pre>
sudo apt install lxd

# use default values everywhere:
sudo lxd init
    </pre>
  </description>
